'''Mike deGruy''' (December 29, 1951 <U+2013> February 4, 2012) was an American [[documentary film]]maker specialising in [[Underwater videography|underwater cinematography]]. His credits include ''[[Life in the Freezer]]'', ''[[Trials of Life]]'', ''[[The Blue Planet]]'' and ''[[Pacific Abyss]]''.

==Death==
In 2012, he was killed in a helicopter crash at Jaspers Brush near the town of [[Berry, New South Wales|Berry]] in [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. The crash also claimed the life of Australian filmmaker [[Andrew Wight]].<ref>[http://newswatch.nationalgeographic.com/2012/02/05/celebrated-filmmakers-killed-in-australian-helicopter-crash/ Celebrated Filmmakers Killed in Australian Helicopter Crash] ''National Geographic,'' February 5, 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/top-filmmakers-mike-degruy-and-andrew-wight-have-died-in-a-nsw-chopper-crash/story-e6frg6nf-1226263094308 Top filmmakers Mike deGruy and Andrew Wight have died in a NSW chopper crash] ''The Australian,'' February 5, 2012</ref>

